$ Oracle: DBA_TAB_COLUMNS
@ dba_tab_columns

`dba_tab_columns` stores information about → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/columns[columns] of
→ development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables[tables],
→ development/databases/Oracle/objects/views[views] and
→ development/databases/Oracle/objects/clusters[clusters]

This view comes in three variants: `user_tab_columns`, `all_tab_columns` and ` dba_tab_columns`.

`dba_tab_columns` is related to → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/tab/cols[`dba_tab_cols`], the difference being that `dba_tab_columns` only shows columns that are
not generated, see → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/tab/columns/diff-tab_cols[differences between `dba_tab_columns` and `dba_tab_cols`]

sa:
  Using `dba_tab_columns` to select the → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/columns/diff-structure[structural differences between two tables].

  A simple investigation into the columns → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/tab/columns/data_length-precision-scale[`DATA_LENGTH`, `DATA_PRECISION` and `DATA_SCALE`]

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/tab/col_statistics[`xxx_TAB_COL_STATISTICS`]

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/source[`dba_source`].
